cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence-to-sequence attentional-based neural network architectures for machine translation and speech recognition. It may also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes a structured-based curriculum learning strategy for training the model. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of neural networks for speech translation. It may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for learning and optimization.
